The TCM test succeeds at offset 0x0440, but queue 31 ignores its semaphore
push and stays at count zero. This suggests that Berlin2CD implements only
the eight HBO queues Valve uses, rather than all 32 queues in the generic
register block.

Repeat the same bounded test on implemented queue 7. Stop dHub channel 3
before borrowing its data queue, clear and configure queue 7 at depth one,
then run the existing TCM readback and 0-1-0 push/pop test. On cleanup,
restore queue 7's Valve base and depth before restarting channel 3.

If clearing or cleanup times out, leave the channel stopped rather than
restart a potentially inconsistent queue. The normal PIO identification
path is independent of pBridge and can continue. This test submits no dHub
descriptor or NAND command.

